==Reception==

===Critical reception===
The film received very positive reviews upon release. Review aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reports that 92% of critics have given the film a positive review based on 81 reviews, with an average score of 7.9/10. The critical consensus is "Blending top notch animation with rousing adventure, witty dialogue, and memorable characters, ''A Bug's Life'' is another Pixar winner."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bugs_life/|title=A Bug's Life Movie Reviews, Pictures |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=June&nbsp;7, 2009}}</ref> Another review aggregator, [[Metacritic]], which assigns a normalized rating out of 100 top reviews from mainstream critics, calculated a score of 77 based on 23 reviews."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/a-bugs-life/|title=A Bug's Life Reviews, Ratings, and more at Metacritic|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=July&nbsp;22, 2011}}</ref>

Todd McCarthy of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' gave the film a positive review, saying "Lasseter and Pixar broke new technical and aesthetic ground in the animation field with ''[[Toy Story]]'', and here they surpass it in both scope and complexity of movement while telling a story that overlaps ''[[Antz]]'' in numerous ways."<ref>{{cite web|author=Todd McCarthy |url=http://variety.com/1998/film/reviews/a-bug-s-life-1200455803/ |title=A Bug<U+2019>s Life |publisher=Variety |date=1998-11-29 |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> [[James Berardinelli]] of ''[[ReelViews]]'' gave the film three and a half stars out of four, saying "''A Bug's Life'', like ''Toy Story'', develops protagonists we can root for, and places them in the midst of a fast-moving, energetic adventure."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reelviews.net/php_review_template.php?identifier=149 |title=Reelviews Movie Reviews |publisher=Reelviews.net |date=1998-11-25 |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> [[Roger Ebert]] of the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' gave the film three and a half stars out of four, saying "Will ''A Bug's Life'' suffer by coming out so soon after ''Antz''? Not any more than one thriller hurts the chances for the next one. ''Antz'' may even help business for ''A Bug's Life'' by demonstrating how many dramatic and comedic possibilities can be found in an anthill."<ref>{{cite web|last=Monji |first=Jana |url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/a-bugs-life-1998 |title=A Bug's Life Movie Review & Film Summary (1998) |publisher=Roger Ebert |date= |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> Kenneth Turan of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' gave the film four out of five stars, saying "What ''A Bug's Life'' demonstrates is that when it comes to bugs, the most fun ones to hang out with hang exclusively with the gang at Pixar."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bugs_life/reviews/?type=top_critics |title=A Bug's Life - Movie Reviews |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |date= |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> Peter Stack of the ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' gave the film four out of four stars, saying "''A Bug's Life''" is one of the great movies -- a triumph of storytelling and character development, and a whole new ballgame for computer animation. Pixar Animation Studios has raised the genre to an astonishing new level.<ref>{{cite web|author=Peter Stack |url=http://www.sfgate.com/movies/article/Bug-s-Has-Legs-Cute-insect-adventure-a-visual-2976395.php |title="Bug's" Has Legs / Cute insect adventure a visual delight |publisher=SFGate |date=1998-11-25 |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> Richard Corliss of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' gave the film a positive review, saying "The plot matures handsomely; the characters neatly converge and combust; the gags pay off with emotional resonance."<ref>{{cite web|last=Corliss |first=Richard |url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,989666,00.html?promoid=googlep |title=Cinema: Bugs Funny - TIME |publisher=Content.time.com |date=1998-11-30 |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> [[Owen Gleiberman]] of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave the film a B, saying "''A Bug's Life'' may be the single most amazing film I've ever seen that I couldn't fall in love with."<ref>{{cite web|author=Owen Gleiberman |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,63798,00.html |title=A Bug's Life Review &#124; Movie Reviews and News |publisher=EW.com |date=1998-11-20 |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> Paul Clinton of ''[[CNN]]'' gave the film a positive review, saying "''A Bug's Life'' is a perfect movie for the holidays. It contains a great upbeat message ... it's wonderful to look at ... it's wildly inventive ... and it's entertaining for both adults and kids."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/SHOWBIZ/Movies/9811/20/review.bugs.life/ |title=Review: 'A Bug's Life' hits a bulls-eye - November 20, 1998 |publisher=CNN |date=1998-11-20 |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> On the contrary, Stephen Hunter of ''[[The Washington Post]]'' gave the film a negative review, saying "Clever as it is, the film lacks charm. One problem: too many bugs. Second, bigger world for two purposes: to feed birds and to irk humans."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/style/movies/reviews/bugslifehunter.htm?movieslede=y |title='A Bug's Life' (G) |publisher=Washingtonpost.com |date=1998-11-25 |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref>

===Box office===
''A Bug's Life'' grossed approximately $33,258,052 on its opening weekend, ranking number 1 for that weekend.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=1998&wknd=48&p=.htm |title=Weekend Box Office Results for November 27-29, 1998 |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date= |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> It managed to retain its number 1 spot for two weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=1998&wknd=49&p=.htm |title=Weekend Box Office Results for December 4-6, 1998 |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date= |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=1998&wknd=50&p=.htm |title=Weekend Box Office Results for December 11-13, 1998 |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date= |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> The film grossed $162.7&nbsp;million in its United States theatrical run, covering its estimated production costs of $120&nbsp;million.<ref name="mojo"/> The film made $200,600,000 in foreign countries, pushing its worldwide gross to $363.3&nbsp;million, surpassing the competition from [[DreamWorks Animation]]'s ''[[Antz]]''.<ref name="mojo"/>

===Awards===
{{Main|List of Pixar awards and nominations (feature films)#A Bug's Life}}

===American Film Institute===
The [[American Film Institute]] nominated ''A Bug's Life'' for its [[AFI's 10 Top 10#Animation|Top 10 Animated Films list]].<ref>[http://www.afi.com/drop/ballot.pdf AFI's 10 Top 10 Ballot]</ref>

==Home media==
''A Bug's Life'' was released on VHS and DVD on April 20, 1999.<ref name="blu-ray1">{{cite web|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/A-Bugs-Life-DVD/24064/ |title=A Bug's Life DVD |publisher=Blu-ray.com |date=1999-04-20 |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> On May 27, 2003, another DVD was released as a 2-disc Collector's Edition.<ref name="blu-ray1"/> This DVD was fully remastered and has substantial bonus features.<ref name="blu-ray1"/> On May 19, 2009, the film was released on [[Blu-ray]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/A-Bugs-Life-Blu-ray/3440/ |title=A Bug's Life Blu-ray |publisher=Blu-ray.com |date= |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref>

==Media and merchandise==

===Attached short film===
{{Main|Geri's Game}}
The film's theatrical and video releases include ''Geri's Game'', a Pixar short made in 1997, a year before this film was released.<ref>{{cite news| last= Maslin| first= Janet| title= A Bug's Life (1998)|url=http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9C02E7DA1639F936A15752C1A96E958260|accessdate=6 May 2012| newspaper=The New York Times|date=25 November 1998}}</ref>

===Video game===
{{Main|A Bug's Life (video game)}}

===Theme park attractions===
''[[A Bug's Land]]'' is a section of [[Disney California Adventure]] is entirely dedicated to ''A Bug's Life''. One of the main attractions is the [[Three-dimensional space|3D]] show ''[[It's Tough to Be a Bug!]]'' which is also in [[Walt Disney World|Walt Disney World Resort]]'s [[Disney's Animal Kingdom]]. The [[Disney California Adventure]] attraction ''[[World of Color]]'' features a segment focused on ''A Bug's Life''.

